Defect 1 — Plist example is fabricated.
- Goose's example plist included `StartInterval=300`,
  `UserName=admin`, `GroupName=admin`,
  `StandardOutPath=/var/log/launchd-ollama.log`.
- Verifying against `docker/launchd-agents/com.iap.ollama.plist`
  (the file Goose cited as source for this example):
  - Actual file is 28 content lines (Goose cited "1-27").
  - Actual file has `KeepAlive=true` (lines 21-22), no
    `StartInterval`. Ollama is a daemon, not periodic.
  - Actual file has NO `UserName` / `GroupName` fields.
    None of the three example plists in the prompt's context
    list contain these fields.
  - Actual `StandardOutPath` is
    `/Users/admin/Library/Logs/iap/com.iap.ollama.out.log`
    (line 24); actual `StandardErrorPath` is
    `/Users/admin/Library/Logs/iap/com.iap.ollama.err.log`
    (line 26). Goose's example collapsed both to
    `/var/log/launchd-ollama.log` — training-data autocomplete
    shape.
  - Actual file has `OLLAMA_HOST=0.0.0.0:11434` env var
    (lines 16-17). Goose's example dropped this.
  - `GroupName` in Goose's example uses `admin`; the migration
    script applies `GroupName=staff` (line 45) at install time.
    Even Goose's fabricated value doesn't match the install-
    time normalization.
- Same shape as Session 8 defect (plausible-shape autocomplete
  from training data when source files contain the actual
  values). Severe.

